<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2669841>
    dc:description "FIGURE 56. Holotype of Scyliorhinus meadi Springer, 1966, USNM 188049, male, 267 mm TL (Florida, United States, 28°21’N 79°51’W). A, dorsal view; B, lateral view. Scale bar = 20 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2669841/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2669843>
    dc:description "FIGURE 57. Scyliorhinus meadi; dorsal view. A, MCZ 42986, female, 185 mm TL (Florida, United States, 28°21’N, 79°51’W); B, UF 107118, female, 252 mm TL (Florida, United States, 28°36’N, 79°51’W); C, USNM 188051, male, 190 mm TL (Florida, United States, 29°44’N, 80°12’W). Scale bar = 20 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2669843/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2669845>
    dc:description "FIGURE 58. Scyliorhinus meadi. A, UF 29835, female, 390 mm TL (North Carolina, United States, 34°12.7’N, 75°51.5’W); B, UF 42186, female, 419 mm TL (Florida, United States, 28°59.51’N, 79°55.29’W); C–E, USNM 188051, male, 190 mm TL (Florida, United States, 29°44’N, 80°12’W); F, UF 166596, male, 720 mm TL (North Carolina, United States). A, B, ventral view of head; C, detail of pectoral fins; D, lateral view of head; E, dorsal view of head; F, detail of pelvic fins and claspers. Scale bar = 20 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2669845/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2669847>
    dc:description "FIGURE 59. Teeth of Scyliorhinus meadi; labial view, USNM 221594, male, 271 mm TL (Bahamas, 24°48’N, 79°17’W). a, anterior tooth; c, commissural; l, lateral. Scale bar = 100 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2669847/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2669849>
    dc:description "FIGURE 60. Dermal denticles of Scyliorhinus meadi. A–B, UF 29835, female, 390 mm TL (North Carolina, United States, 34°12.7’N, 75°51.5’W); D–F, USNM 221594, male, 271 mm TL (Bahamas, 24°48’N, 79°17’W). A, D, region above pectoral fin base; B, E, region below first dorsal fin origin; C, F, region below second dorsal fin insertion. Scale bar = 250 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2669849/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2669851>
    dc:description "FIGURE 61. Clasper of Scyliorhinus meadi; dorsal view, UF 166596, 720 mm TL (North Carolina, United States). ap, apopyle; crh, cover rhipidion; erh, exorhipidion; hp, hipopyle; rh, rhipidion; tdc, terminal dermal cover. Scale bar = 20 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2669851/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2669853>
    dc:description "FIGURE 62. Map showing the geographic distribution of Scyliorhinus meadi based on material examined in this study. Black star indicates the type locality." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2669853/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

